Test-case name: xfdesktop-settings/xfdesktop-settings-001
Testing settings window launch correctly.
<dl>
    <dt>Right-click on desktop and click 'Desktop Settings...</dt>
    <dt>Observe that the Desktop Settings window opens.</dt>
</dl>

Test-case name: xfdesktop-settings/xfdesktop-settings-002
Testing wallpaper changes correctly.
<dl>
    <dt>Under 'Background', Ensure 'Image' is set to 'Single image'.</dt>
    <dt>Click on a wallpaper other than the one currently selected.</dt>
    <dt>Observe that the wallpaper has changed accordingly.</dt>
</dl>

Test-case name: xfdesktop-settings/xfdesktop-settings-003
Testing custom wallpaper.
<dl>
    <dt>Click on the green plus (+) button. A dialog should open.</dt>
    <dt>Choose a background image in an appropiate format (png or jpeg recommended).</dt>
    <dt>Observe that the added background is set correctly.</dt>
</dl>

Test-case name: xfdesktop-settings/xfdesktop-settings-004
Testing image list functionality.
<dl>
    <dt>Under 'Background', Ensure 'Image' is set to 'Image list'.</dt>
    <dt>Add images to the list by clicing the plus button as before.</dt>
    <dt>Observe that added images change correctly.</dt>
    <dt>Select an image and click the red minus (-) button.</dt>
    <dt>Observe that the image is removed from the list.</dt>
</dl>

Test-case name: xfdesktop-settings/xfdesktop-settings-005
Testing colours and gradients.
<dl>
    <dt>Under 'Background', ensure 'Image' is set to 'None'.</dt>
    <dt>Under the 'Colours' drop down menu, select and observe the effect of 'Solid colour', 'Horizontal gradient', 'Vertical gradient', and 'Transparent' each in turn, ensuring each are applied correctly.</dt>
    <dt>Change the colour(s) for each, and observe that they are set correctly</dt>
</dl>

Test-case name: xfdesktop-settings/xfdesktop-settings-006
Testing colour adjustments.
<dl>
    <dt>Increase and decrease the value of the 'Brightness' slider and observe that the brightness changes accordingly.</dt>
    <dt>Increase and decrease the value of the 'Saturation' slider and observe that the saturation changes accordingly.</dt>
</dl>

Test-case name: xfdesktop-settings/xfdesktop-settings-007
Testing desktop menu.
<dl>
    <dt>Right click on the desktop, and observe that the 'Applications' menu loads up a list of applications correctly.</dt>
    <dt>In the desktop settings, under 'Menus', untick and retick the 'Show applications menu on desktop right click' box and observing in turn that it shows and hides the applications menu correctly.</dt>
    <dt>Untick and retick the 'Show application icons in menu' box, observing that it shows and hides the application icons in the desktop menu.</dt>
    <dt>Middle (scroll) click on the desktop and observe that a window list appears.</dt>
    <dt>Untick and recheck each of the boxes under 'Window List Menu' in the desktop settings dialog, ensuring that they each enable and disable their labelled functions.</dt>
</dl>

Test-case name: xfdesktop-settings/xfdesktop-settings-008
Testing desktop icons.
<dl>
   <dt>Under the 'Icons' tab of the desktop settings manager, under 'Appearance', change icon type to 'Minimised application icons' and ensure the desktop icons now represent the currently running applications.</dt>
   <dt>Now change icon type to none and observe that all desktop icons disappear. They should reappear upon reselecting 'File/launcher icons'.</dt>
   <dt>Change the icon size with the up and down buttons and observe that the icons change size correctly. Check that manually entering a value also has the required effect.</dt>
   <dt>Click the check box 'Use custom font size' and ensure that using the up or down arrows, or entering a value, changes the icon font size correctly. Unchecking the box should restore the font size to default.</dt>
   <dt>Untick and retick 'Show thumbnails' and observe that desktop thumbnails are shown and hidden correctly (may need some video or image files on the desktop to check this).</dt>
   <dt>Tick 'Single click to activate icons' and ensure that the icon applications now launch upon being clicked. Untick the box and ensure it now functions as before (double click).</dt>
   <dt>Tick and untick each of the checkboxes under 'Default Icons', ensuring each in turn is hidden and shown.</dt>
</dl>

<strong>If all actions produce the expected results listed, and you can answer yes to the above questions, please <a href="results#add_result">submit</a> a 'passed' result.
    If an action fails, or produces an unexpected result, or you answer no to any of the above questions, please <a href="results#add_result">submit</a> 'failed' and <a href="../../buginstructions">file a bug</a>. Please be sure to include the bug number when you <a href="results#add_result">submit</a> your result</strong>